%description:
Tests D-SACK-based loss-recovery undo (RFC 2883, lossUndoEnabled=true). One
mid-stream data segment is DELAYED (not lost). The later segments still arrive
and generate DupThresh duplicate ACKs, so TcpReno enters fast recovery and
spuriously retransmits the delayed segment. When the delayed original finally
arrives the receiver already has that data, so it reports a D-SACK for the
duplicate. The sender recognizes that every retransmission of the episode was
unnecessary and undoes the cwnd/ssthresh reduction.

%inifile: omnetpp.ini
[General]
record-vector-results = false
ned-path = .;../../../../src;../../lib

network = inet.test.moduletest.lib.TcpTestNet1

cmdenv-event-banners=false
cmdenv-express-mode=false
cmdenv-log-prefix="[%c]: "

*.testing=false

*.tcptester.script="A8 delay 0.008"

*.cli_app.active=true
*.cli_app.localAddress="10.0.0.1"
*.cli_app.localPort=1000
*.cli_app.connectAddress="10.0.0.2"
*.cli_app.connectPort=2000
*.cli_app.tOpen=0s
*.cli_app.tSend=0s
*.cli_app.sendBytes=15000B
*.cli_app.sendScript=""
*.cli_app.tClose=-1s

*.srv_app.active=false
*.srv_app.localAddress="10.0.0.2"
*.srv_app.localPort=2000
*.srv_app.connectAddress="10.0.0.1"
*.srv_app.connectPort=1000
*.srv_app.tOpen=0s
*.srv_app.tSend=-1s
*.srv_app.sendBytes=0B
*.srv_app.sendScript=""
*.srv_app.tClose=-1s

*.*_tcp.advertisedWindow = 10000
*.*_tcp.sackSupport = true
*.*_tcp.timestampSupport = false
*.*_tcp.mss = 500
*.*_tcp.tcpAlgorithmClass = "TcpReno"
*.*_tcp.lossUndoEnabled = true
*.*_tcp.initialWindow = "rfc6928"

%# the sender detects the D-SACK and undoes the spurious reduction, restoring
%# cwnd to its pre-recovery value (8000) and ssthresh to the pre-loss value.
%# Falsification: with lossUndoEnabled=false this line is absent and cwnd stays
%# halved (verified during development).
%contains: stdout
Undoing spurious cwnd reduction (D-SACK): cwnd=8000

%# the transfer completes
%contains: stdout
received 15000 bytes in 15 packets
